A true Bay Ridge gem.... This is the oldest family owned and operated bar in the Ridge dating back to the 1930's. The establishment is split in 2, with the bar in the front serving inexpensive mugs of domestic draught beer and shots. No frills here! However, they do have a dining room in the back and serve excellent pub food at more then reasonable prices. The 8oz burgers are only 7 bucks and are fresh ground beef and home made fries, cooked to order at the temperature you requested. There sandwiches are equally as delicious and reasonably priced as are their entrees. Also, on less busy days, the chef is more then happy to accomidate any request you may have. On a previous visit my boyfriend was craving Salisbury steak (fancy term for a large burger, heavy seasoned and covered in mushroom gravy) and he happily obliged and made him a wonderful dish, it was only 12 bucks about 16oz of meat with mashed potatoes, fresh sauteed vegetables and a salad, this place is a true hidden gem!

You either go to this place because you want to hang with laid back locals, singing Billy Joel at the top of your lungs or because you want a good burger. For ~$7, you get one of the best burgers that is juicy, cooked just as you like (medium, please) with some of the best crispy and salty fries ever. Try the chicken strips and onion rings , too. Not too oily and so crispy with killer buffalo sauce.

The neighborhood bar that isn't an old man bar but isn't full of guidos either. O'Sullivan's is the kind of bar that you go for a quick beer when you get off the subway after work but end up staying for dinner.  Their burgers, fries and onion rings are a must. You may want to try their Shepard's pie as well. The seating area is a bit small in the back but that kind of adds to the charm of the place.  Go forth and enjoy.
